issues.body:
In This sample a AC is requested over existing bearer:

```
{
  "ietf-ac-svc:attachment-circuits": {
    "ac": [
      {
        "name": "ac4585",
        "description": "An AC on an existing bearer",
        "requested-ac-start": "2023-12-12T05:00:00.00Z",
        "l2-connection": {
          "encapsulation": {
            "type": "ietf-vpn-common:dot1q",
            "dot1q": {
              "tag-type": "ietf-vpn-common:c-vlan",
              "cvlan-id": 550
            }
          },
          "bearer-reference": "line-156"
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

To realize this request the controller **should** be aware of the existing bearers in the network.

- If it is a brownfield scenario, the bearer can not be populate so how we consider this attribute can be obtained?

- In greenfield scenarios, this parameter can exist, for example using the L3NM can be assigned in the VP-NETWORK-ACCESS. In this case, the controller should make a reverse lookup to discover the existing bearers in the network and find where to attach the new AC. This can be exahustive in big networks and can limit the usability. 
- As the bearer represents a concept itself can, we consider modeling the bearers? O something similar as Bridge Domain to group  SAPs or ACs?
